./.title: UAV.Monitor+APM  Architecture
./.body:
UAV.Monitor+APM Architecture
Below are core components

Health Manager (HM in short): a data processing program that supports data analysis, storage and query.
Monitor Agent (MA in short): an JSE application with the functionality of data collection and node container control. It collects performance metrics of containers, processes and JAVA applications and delivers the metrics collected to Health Manager.
Monitor Framework(MOF in short): monitors applications without intrusion by integrating with JEE middleware. With javaagent, it supports application profile and performance data collection.

healthmanager.html.title: Health Manager
healthmanager.html.body:
Health Manager
HM Architecture
1. Overall architecture and characteristics
HM(HealthManager) is a comprehensive service center that supports the processing of the monitoring data, the profile data, the runtime notification data and log data. It calculates and processes all data in the UAVStack and provides related service support. Below is the overall architecture of HM: 

Below are characteristics of HM: 

HM is a deployable JAVA MAIN process program
Each HM could integrate multiple features, each of which is with the single responsibility. Users shall customize the HM process by integrating features needed by the business 
HM can be deployed on different hosts based on the needs of users, forming an HM cluster
The service interface of HM is visible to the higher level (business and other systems).

2. HM workflow
Below are the overall workflow of HM: 

In UAVStack, MA collects the monitor data and profile data (except the heartbeat data) and delivers the data to the information middleware RocketMQ. Each feature in HM consumes its corresponding data and persists the data into different databases based on the message type. For instance, the monitoring server shall consume the monitor data in RocketMQ and persist the data into OpenTSDB while the profile data shall consume the profile data and persist the data into MongoDB. Refer to details in HM service. HM shall expose Http service interfaces, with which AppHub shall query and display data. Some external systems could access the monitoring data with such interfaces.

healthmanager/hmfu-wu.html.title: HM Servers
healthmanager/hmfu-wu.html.body:
HM service
As micro-service architecture, HM are with separable features as below: 

Heartbeat Server
Profile Server
Monitor Server
Node Server
Runtime Server
Notification Server
AppHub Manager
Log Server
Invocation Chain / Thread Analysis Server

healthmanager/xin-tiao-shu-ju-fu-wu.html.title: Heartbeat Data Server
healthmanager/xin-tiao-shu-ju-fu-wu.html.body:
Heartbeat Server
Heartbeat Server processes the heartbeat data of MSCP applications. Below are detailed workflow: 

Heartbeat Server receives the heartbeat data packages from MSCP nodes (including HM) via the internally integrated HTTPserver and stores such data in Redis to help spot MSCP nodes. The heartbeat data includes relevant information (including the use of CPU, memory and disk) about the node container. Heartbeat Server periodically captures time stamps of the last heartbeat of nodes to compare with the current time and determine whether the node is alive. In addition, Heartbeat Server exposes the query interfaces for heartbeat data query by external applications via http://ip:port/hb/query.

healthmanager/hua-xiang-shu-ju-fu-wu.htm.title: Profile Data Server
healthmanager/hua-xiang-shu-ju-fu-wu.htm.body:
Profile Server
Profile Server consumes the profile data in RocketMQ. Below are detailed workflow: 

Profile Server consumes the profile data in RocketMQ delivered by MA, stores the data in MongoDB, and caches the data within 5 minutes in Redis. Profile Server also redelivers the profile data to RocketMQ and the redelivered data is finally further consumed by Runtime Server for the notification information calculation. In addition, Profile Server exposes the query interfaces for profile data query by external applications via http://ip:port/hm/cache/q.

healthmanager/shi-shi-shu-ju-fu-wu.html.title: Monitoring Data Server
healthmanager/shi-shi-shu-ju-fu-wu.html.body:
Monitoring Server
Monitoring Server consumes the monitor data in RocketMQ. Below are detailed workflow: 

Monitoring Server consumes the monitor data in RocketMQ delivered by MA, stores the data in OpenTSDB, and caches the data within 5 minutes in Redis. Monitoring Server also redelivers the monitor data to RocketMQ and the redelivered data is finally further consumed by Runtime Server for the notification information calculation. In addition, Monitoring Server exposes the query interfaces for monitor data query within 5 minutes via http://ip:port/hm/cache/q and for earlier data query via http://ip:port/hm/query by external applications.

healthmanager/rong-qi-jie-dian-shu-ju-fu.title: Node Data Server
healthmanager/rong-qi-jie-dian-shu-ju-fu.body:
Node Server
Node Server consumes the nodeinfon data in RocketMQ. Below are detailed workflow: 

Node Server consumes the nodeinfo data in RocketMQ delivered by Runtime Server and stores the data in OpenTSDB. In addition, Profile Server exposes the query interfaces for node data query by external applications via http://ip:port/hm/query.

healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu.html.title: Runtime Notification Server
healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu.html.body:
Runtime Server
Runtime Server determines whether or not the notification event shall be generated based on the pulled notification data.


Pull the notification data from RocketMQ and the notification strategies from Redis for comparison and determine whether or not the notification event shall be generated;  

Deliver the notification event to RocketMQ.

healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.title: Notification Data Structure
healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.body:
Structure of the notification data
The structure of the notification data is saved and processed in a time slice.

Properties of the slice include key, timestamp, map that stores mdf, and mdf properties.
Each slice stores a small section of MDF information and a slice is sampled for the given time span.

Obtain continuous slices with getSlice (Slice, start, end) function and have them processed by the notification strategy.

healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.title: Notification Strategy
healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.body:
Notification strategy
Process the notification information based on the notification strategy and determine to generate notification event or not. Below is a notification strategy: 

In the picture above, “range” refers to the time span of end-start and “function” is used for the evalution of specific function values, such as avg, sum, max and min.

healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.title: Notification Strategy Expressions
healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.body:
Notification strategy expression:

Generate notification strategy expressions with CPU, memory, connection count, monitoring throughput, error frequency of logs and JVM MGC frequency and determine to generate notification event or not.

healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.title: Notification Format
healthmanager/shi-shi-yu-jing-fu-wu/yu-j.body:
Notification format
Below is the mail and sms format for the notification event to be sent:

healthmanager/yu-jing-zhong-xin-fu-wu.ht.title: Notification Server
healthmanager/yu-jing-zhong-xin-fu-wu.ht.body:
Notification Server
Notification Server determines whether to send the notification message or not based on the notification event.The notification server pulls notifications from RocketMQ to HM. HM makes decisions about notification events based on the delivery time of notifications or are notifications repeated ones. Configure the delivery mode between SMS and mail, decide whether to send out notifications or not, and save the nitifications in MongoDB.
Decision-making flow of Notification Server

Notification decision-making flow: abstract the primary key of the notification event delivered by Runtime Server. The primary key is composed of eventID, IP and create-time.Determine whehter the notification information exists or not based on the primary key; if yes, determine whether the notification information expires or not; if no, then determine whether the repetition frequency exceeds the maximum value or not. Invoke the mail module and the sms module and send the notification if all conditions are met.

healthmanager/apphubfu-wu.html.title: AppHub Server
healthmanager/apphubfu-wu.html.body:
AppHub
AppHub reads and writes information related to AppHub from databases.

As shown in the picture, 
Web AppHub supports user login, UAV management and service governance management (i.e. monitoring authorization) by obtaining service governance data (monitoring authorization) information, App information cache, AppHub management cache and user information cache written into it by Redis. 
AppHub reads / writes App information, AppHub management information and AppHubDataStore infomation into MongoDB.

healthmanager/ri-zhi-fu-wu.html.title: Log Data Server
healthmanager/ri-zhi-fu-wu.html.body:
Log Server
Monitor Server consumes the log data in RocketMQ. Below are detailed workflow: 

Log Server consumes the log data in RocketMQ delivered by MA and stores the data in ElasticSearch. Log Server also redelivers the log data to RocketMQ and the redelivered data is finally further consumed by Runtime Server for the notification information calculation. In addition, Log Server exposes the query interfaces for log data query by external applications via http://ip:port/newlog/q.

monitoragent.html.title: Monitor Agent
monitoragent.html.body:
监控代理程序
MA架构
MA的实现架构如下图所示：

MA是一个agent，用于解耦，在application外独立运行。MA用于定时抓取MOF中的信息、自动发现Tomcat、MSCP、JavaEE中的信息并获取更多推导的监控信息。之后MA中的数据通过Rocketmq到达HealthManager。
MA获取的值来自两部分：

MonitorFramework在J2EE工程中埋点，MA从中取值
MA从系统中获取参数值

MA的运行机制为：


MSCPBoot作为MSCP的程序入口，在启动时调用SystemStarter的startup方法。
在SystemStarter启动时会调用MonitorAgent的start方法，在此方法中调用AppServerMonitorDetector的run方法。
在run方法中获取所有的JVM进程，并启动对应数据的抓取任务及判断是否占用性能太多而需要自杀。
在AppServerMonitorDetector的addWorker方法中，根据jvmType的不同值来定时抓取Tomcat/MSCP/JavaSE的Monitor Data并生成MonitorDataFrame。
若无法获取Monitor Data，运行进程检测，若进程死掉，则相关worker自动退出。
将MonitorDataFrame发送到Rocketmq，最终到达HealthManager进行处理。其中收集的消息分为profile数据和monitor数据，前者为系统静态数据，后者为实时监控数据。

monitoragent/xin-tiao-ji-zhi.html.title: Heartbeat Mechanism
monitoragent/xin-tiao-ji-zhi.html.body:
Heartbeat mechanism
The heartbeat mechanism is the basis for service registration in service governance. Below is the class diagram of the heartbeat mechanism: 

As shown above, there are both the client-side heartbeat mechanism and the server-side heartbeat mechnism.

The client side generates the contents of heartbeat messages and send them to the server side via Http every 15 minutes by default.
Contents of messages:

Module and Http services started by the MSCP node; 
Context data: OS information, JDK information and disk use;
Context performance data: CPU, memory, conncetion count, port traffic and disk IO.
Life cycle of the client side: Alive (1*TTL, green) —> Dying (2*TTL, red) —> Dead (5*TTL, grey)—> Disappear (10*TTL)


The server side stores the contents of the heartbeat messages and the cascading with the multi-level service registration center.
Storage: CacheManager hash structure:
node.info:
key: NodeInfo.id,
value: NodeInfo JSON
Cascading: Multi-level service registration center.
The low tolerance towards the update latency of the service registration information in particular business scenarios makes the computational node of the heartbeat cascading a service registration center.

monitoragent/ying-yong-shu-ju-cai-ji.htm.title: Application Data Collection
monitoragent/ying-yong-shu-ju-cai-ji.htm.body:
Application data collection

Self-detection workflow:
In the start method of MonitorAgent 

Create and start the AppServerMonitorDetector instance, obtain  all JVM processes with the run method, and start the data fetching task.
Create the AppServerMonitorDetector instance and start a thread to collect the profile data.
Start MDFListener to receive MDF or MDF array pushed by the third-party so as to collect the monitoring data.


Periodical fetching workflow: 
Includes AppServerMonitorDataCatchWorker (Tomcat), MSCPMonitorDataCatchWorker (MSCP) and JavaMonitorDataCatchWorker (JavaSE). Take Tomcat as an example: 
In the run method of AppServerMonitorDataCatchWorker

Obtain all MBean corresponding to Monitor with the doCaptureMonitorData method and store all Mbean into MDF.
Process data with the detector.runHandlers method.
Obtain all MBean corresponding to Profile with the doCaptureProfileData method and store all Mbean into MDF.
Display the profile data with apdc.putData.

wherein, Mbean is classified into different types: 

MBean queried by AppServer/MSCP: 
profile: "com.creditease:feature=profiles,*"
monitor: "com.creditease:feature=monitors,*"



MBean queried by Java:
"java.lang.management"
ClassLoadingMXBean
MemoryMXBean
MemoryPoolMXBean
“com.sun.management."
GarbageCollectorMXBean
ThreadMXBean
OperatingSystemMXBean
UnixOperatingSystemMXBean

monitoragent/ying-yong-shu-ju-cai-ji/yin.title: Application Monitoring Data
monitoragent/ying-yong-shu-ju-cai-ji/yin.body:
Monitoring data

Source
Obtain the monitor data from the run method of AppServerMonitorDataCatchWorker and JavaMonitorDataCatchWorker by calling doCaptureMonitorData and store the monitor data into MDF.

Operation
The monitor data is processed by calling the corresponding handlers (such as MonitorDataPublishHandler and DefaultNotificationEventHandler, which can be configured in agent.properties) in the run method of AppServerMonitorDataCatchWorker.

MOF Agent
Component diagram of MOF Agent 

Main principle of MOF Agent:
Transfer the logic that the pre-loaded codes monitor businesses with JavaAgent

Core components:MOFAgentMOFClsTransformerMOFAdaptorMOFInterceptor

Core technologies:JavaAgentJavassist


Hook principle of MOF Agent TomCat/MSCP

TomcatAdaptor/MSCPAdaptor hooking:
TomcatAdaptor/MSCPAdaptor has two methods, namely onStartup and onLoadClass:onStartup loads the targeted hook class and builts in bytecodes during the initialization;onLoadClass hooks codes in the business logic and builts in bytecodes of the UAV monitoring codes.

TomcatIT/MSCPIT parsing:
TomcatIT/MSCPIT correponds to class loading and configuration file initialization when TomcatAdaptor/MSCPIT executes onStartup.

TomcatPlusIT/MSCPPlusIT parsing:
TomcatPlusIT/MSCPPlusIT corresponds to different classes that execute onLoadClass in TomcatAdaptor/MSCPPlusIT and the monitoring logic executed in the method.

Key hook targets and functionality of Tomcat/MSCP:Key hook targets of Tomcat:Bootstrap(createClassLoader)-->Tomcat loads MOFJar package during initialization and initializes the configuration fileConnector(invoke)-->Tomcat executes the MOF monitoring logic with the onServiceStart method
Key hook targets of MSCP:MSCPBoot(createBootClassLoader): corresponds to the initialization of MOFJar package when MSCP is loadedSystemStarter(startServer): corresponds to the MOF monitoring logic executed by the system

moniorframework/shi-shi-shu-ju-sheng-che.title: Monitoring Data Collection
moniorframework/shi-shi-shu-ju-sheng-che.body:
Monitoring data capturing
Monitoring data
Also refered to as the runtime data generated when the process runs, including CPU use, heap memory, JVM information and statistics information (average response time and access count) related to service access and client-side invocation.
Service data collection
The service data collection takes DefaultMonitorSupporter.start as the access point and builds the monitor instance (StandardMonitor instance of the server type by default, including the StandardMonitorRepository instance and the uavlog instance). The StandardMonitorRepository instance registers with the monitor. A StandardMonitorRepository instance includes multiple MonitorElement instances which are saved in the elemsMap property.
The elemsMap property saves different collection handlers based on different collection objects:

ServerEndRespTimeCapHandler: collects the response time and loading count of Server, App and URL.
JVMStateCapHandler: collects JVM conditions, including heap use, GC count, thread count, CPU and class count.

Client-side data collection
The service data collection takes DefaultClientMonitorSupporter.start as the access point and builds the monitor instance (StandardMonitor instance of the client type by default, including the StandardMonitorRepository instance and the uavlog instance). The StandardMonitorRepository instance registers with the monitor. A StandardMonitorRepository instance includes multiple MonitorElement instances which are saved in the elemsMap property.
The elemsMap property saves only one colletion handler: 

ClientRespTimeCapHandler: collects the response time and loading count of the client side.

moniorframework/hua-xiang-shu-ju-cai-ji..title: Profile Data Collection
moniorframework/hua-xiang-shu-ju-cai-ji..body:
Profile data collection
Profile data
Also refered to as the static data generated when the process starts, including information related to the operation system and processes as well as the initializtion information after the process starts.
Start InterceptFrameworkSupportor with the start method. Add listener to the listener property of the InterceptSupportor instance first, traverse listeners of InterceptSupporter with JavaAgent tracking and invoke the doIntercept method. In this method, invoke the handleEvent method of InterceptEventListener. InterceptEventListener is the parent class of all listeners. Different subclasses process different profile collections.

Service profile collection
The service profile describes information about the service itself, including AppID, Service ID, URI of the service instance, the metadata (class, method, input and output parameters, annotation and deployment descriptor) of the service interface.
The AppProfilingListener collects the service profile. The handleEvent method invokes the startProfiling method to start the profile and completes the collection with StandardProfile.doProfiling.
Please refer to com.creditease.uav.profiling.handlers.ComponentProfileHandler for detailed codes of the service profile.

Provenance data collection
Fields in the Header of the Http protocol can help with the provenance. Data collected can be classified as below: 

Client Address: IP of the directly connected client side


X-Forwarded-For: addresses of the proxy routing if any. Then the directly connected client side would be the proxy service


Host: display the remote host, even the port information. The host shall be the proxy IP address and port if the directly connected client side is the proxy service


User-Agent: agent description that distinguishes browsers from clients and abstracts the terminal information of browsers


UAV-Client-Src: header added during Http client hooking. The header is used for the fitting of invocation among applications


Client-side profile collection
The client-side profile is implemented by hooking the the client sides of multiple frequently used middleware. It supports synchronous / asynchronous Http, jdbc, Redis(jedis,aredis,lettuce), MongoDB and RocketMQ/rabbitmq.
Embed the processing logic of UAV in the calling code of the client side with AOP technologies (such as the rewriting of the javassist bytecode and the dynamic proxy) and obtain relevant invocation, including the invocation address, the invocation protocol and the invocation results.
The profile data determines the target service based on the invocation address, access protocol and characteristics of the invocation result.
1) Invocation address: expressed in the format similar to URI

http/https service (business / proxy service):  : /http://:/ path>
Relational database (data source service):jdbc:://:,:/
Non-relational database or cache (data source service):jdbc:://:,:/
Message queue (message service): mq:://:/

2) Access protocol: an access action, such as the POST insertion and the SQL insertion of Http, delivering/subscribing information, hgethashall of Redis and collection of Mongo
3) Characteristics of access results: type of the basic stack of the service; cluster (such as ngnix, tomcat and apache) or not
Please refer to com.creditease.uav.profiling.handlers for detailed codes of the client-side profile. ClientRespTimeCapHandler

moniorframework/diao-yong-lian-shu-ju-sh.title: Invocation Chain Data Collection
moniorframework/diao-yong-lian-shu-ju-sh.body:
Invocation Chain Data Generation
The invocation chain is the specific implementation of the domain model of distributed tracing.
The invocation chain records each request and analyzes the invocation process.
Invocation chain model

Invocation chain metadata: 
SpanEndpointType: invocation type (Root(“E”), Service(“S”), Client(“C”), Method(“M”));
traceId: unique identifier of trace;
spanId: invocation sequence of the current node in an invocation chain (unique when combined with SpanEndpointType)
parentId: parent invocation node of current node in an invocation chain.
Invocation chain mapping rules:
1) Register the initial invocation (without parent invocation) of the invoker (service and web) as the starting node E and generate the unique traceID;
2) Add “1” (“.1” if comes as the first one) after the spanID for the invocation among application components (such as httpclient and method invocation) within the system;
3) Span information of Service A and Service B differs in SpanEndpointType only (each representing one end of the span) for the invocation among systems.

Illustration with the example:




traceId;1;N;E
traceId;1.1;1;C
traceId;1.1;1;S
traceId;1.1.1;1.1;C
traceId;1.1.2;1.1;C

Invocation chain architecture

1) Enable or disenable the invocation chain with the inline applets of UAV; 
2) MOF collects the invocation chain information and outputs it to the log files;
3) The collection mechanism of MA uploads logs to the specifized topic in RocketMQ of UAV;
4) The invocation chain handlers in HM analyze and process the invocation chain data in RocketMQ and store the data in ElasticSearch;
5) HM supports the query interfaces for front-end display of the console.
